Getting the sources

* Released versions

 In order to get the source for officially released versions, go to the
 {{{https://www.orekit.org/forge/projects/orekit/files}Files}} tab in Orekit
 forge and select one of the orekit-x.y-src.zip file. The x.y part in the name
 specifies the version. If this is the first time you download the library and
 you have not yet setup you own data set with UTC-TAI history, JPL ephemerides,
 IERS Earth Orientation Parameters ... you may also download the orekit-data.zip
 file which is an example file suitable for a quick start (see
 {{{./configuration.html}configuration}} for further reading about data configuration).

* Development version

 The development of the Orekit project is done using the {{{http://git-scm.com/}Git}}
 source code control system. Orekit Git master repository is available online.

 ** you can browse it using the {{{https://www.orekit.org/forge/projects/orekit/repository}Repository}}
    tab in Orekit forge
 ** you can clone it anonymously with the command:

+-------
git clone http://www.orekit.org/git/orekit
+-------

 ** if you are a committer, you can clone it using your ssh credentials with the command:

+-------
git clone ssh://git@www.orekit.org/orekit.git
+-------
